  "details": "The npm package `ethers-core` version `6.13.7` impersonates an ethers.js utility package but runs an install-time malicious chain. `package.json` declares `postinstall: node dist/index.min.js`. The executed entrypoint reads selected environment secrets and home-directory credential/wallet files, double-encodes collected data, and sends it to Telegram and a configured webhook. It also uses discovered private keys to attempt ETH or BTC transfers to configured recipient wallets, modifies shell startup files, creates a desktop autostart entry, and drops a recurring curl-based payload. This behavior is unrelated to the package's claimed ethers utility purpose.",
